cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE 

This paper proposes an approach to training deep neural networks for text classification that is robust to label noise. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with natural language processing and related tasks. The paper also discusses the use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and regularization techniques, which are common in sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper mentions experiments on image classification datasets, which could suggest a connection to sub-categories such as cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the paper introduces a noise model to handle label noise, which could also relate to sub-category cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
